[{'_id': '284740', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Coriander, also known as Chinese parsley, is considered as an annual herb and a spice. Both its leaves and dried seeds are used as a condiment. The leaves are used as an ingredient in many Indian foods for their rich aroma and lemony citrus flavor.'}, {'_id': '284741', 'specification': 'Benefits', 'value': 'Raw coriander leaves are about 92 per cent water, 2 per cent protein and 4 per cent carbohydrates. They are a rich source of Vitamin C, Vitamin A and Vitamin K with a moderate amount of dietary minerals.  Coriander is known for its anti-inflammatory properties thus aid the treatment of arthritis. It is also good for the digestive system and promotes liver functions and bowel movements.'}, {'_id': '284742', 'specification': 'Storage and Use', 'value': 'Use airtight containers to store the Coriander at home. Exposure to air and heat is a major factor for the deterioration of the flavour and shelf life; hence, it is advisable to store the coriander in an airtight container below 70-degree temperature.   Fresh coriander is used to garnish curry or vegetable dishes. It is also used to add flavor to soups, and chutneys. Coriander seed, which are actually the dried seed of the coriander plant, is used as a spice. Typically used ground, coriander seed has a spicy and citrus flavor.'}, {'_id': '1011494', 'specification': 'Scientific Name', 'value': 'Coriandrum sativum L.'}, {'_id': '1205146', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'CORIANDER'}]

p_description:
Because who does not fall in love with the rich aroma and great taste of Ghee!

Namdhari’s Dairy Tales Pure Cow Ghee is completely processed using modern techniques and has a rich taste of 100% pure cow’s milk. The Ghee is prepared from the cow’s milk at our own farm at Bidadi, Karnataka and hence we ensure the quality of the Ghee remains intact and high with nutrients. We assure responsible dairy farming and hence our cows are taken extra care by feeding with protein and nutrient-rich cattle food.

A research undertaken by the Tata salt team showed that over 40% of the urban adult population in India suffers from hypertension, a life-threatening condition that can be effectively managed by controlling the intake of sodium. To control sodium intake, people diagnosed with hypertension are often advised to reduce or control salt consumption. Due to this, they often have to consume less salt and at times, bland food. In light of these findings, Tata salt Lite was introduced, a low sodium salt that would assist management of blood pressure without compromising on the taste of food. So now, stay healthy and keep your blood pressure in check with Tata salt lite, Desh Ki Sehat, Desh Ka Namak.'}, {'_id': '1250248', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'LITE  '}]

[{'_id': '1236701', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'If you are looking for healthier alternatives for rice, Safe Harvest’s Foxtail Millet would be the product for you. After being ethically procured from small and marginal farmers practicing rain-fed agriculture in Virudhunagar district of Tamil Nadu, our Foxtail Millet have been minimally processed, safely stored and hygienically packed at our processing centres. It is ensured that Safe Harvest’s Foxtail Millet does not go through any polishing or artificial colouring which would otherwise compromise on the nutrition content in the product. Millets are known to highly nutritious, easily digestible and rich in proteins, calcium and other minerals. When compared with rice, barnyard millet has 13% less carbohydrates, is gluten free and has lower levels of glucose. Foxtail Millet could be used to substitute rice in making idly, upma, dosas and several rice items. The consumption of millets not only makes you healthier but also helps farmers practice more sustainable agriculture. Millets, unlike paddy and wheat, are not water intensive crops and would lead to conservation of water right from the farm gate.'}, {'_id': '1249836', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Foxtail Millet Rice 500G'}]

[{'_id': '1236863', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Our rice comes from the Sona Masuri BPT 5204 variety of paddy cultivated by small and marginal farmers practicing chemical pesticide free agriculture in the Krishna irrigated region of the Raichur district in Karnataka. The paddy is stringently tested for quality parameters like moisture content and percentage of broken rice. [{'_id': '1236869', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Our rice comes from the Sona Masuri BPT 5204 variety of paddy cultivated by small and marginal farmers practicing chemical pesticide free agriculture in the Krishna irrigated region of the Raichur district in Karnataka. These farmers adopt the System of Rice Intensification (SRI) technique, which greatly reduces the water footprint of the crop. The paddy is stringently tested for quality parameters like moisture content and percentage of broken rice. The procured paddy is then aged for 12 months to further reduce the moisture content before it is milled into rice. Carefully curated ageing ensures that the rice has an optimum level of moisture translating into a higher yield of the cooked product.'}, {'_id': '1250232', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Sona Masuri Raw Rice 12 Months 1Kg'}]

p_name: Desert Salt Winter Har Sha 100 GM
p_spec:
[{'_id': '1233436', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'USAGE: Healthy Salt For Daily Cooking, Salads, Fruits, Juices & Health Drinks.
No Anti-Caking Agent, Free From Micro-Plastics, Traditionally Hand-Harvested, Raw- Not Processed.
RICH IN MINERALS: Lunn Desert salt is rich in minerals that are important in maintaining a healthy lifestyle like Potassium,Calcium, Iodine, Magnesium, Iron, Phosphorus & Sulphate.
CERTIFIED: Vegan, Gluten Free, Organic Harvest, Non- GMO, Fair Market, True Source & Halal
MILD IN TASTE & LOW ON SODIUM: Being A Mild Salt, It Brings Out Authentic Flavours In Your Food.
DESERT SALT HARVEST PROCESS: The Great Indian Desert, also known as the Thar Desert, situated in the state of Rajasthan, India is the 9th largest subtropical desert in the world. Deep beneath its glistening hot sands, large pools of water form when the rare rains arrive during the monsoon season. As the water seeps down, it combines with the mineral rich desert salt to form a thick saline mixture.This is pumped up and left to dry in the salt pans, creating dunes of one of the purest forms of salts found anywhere. Monsoon rains replenish the water levels each season creating a sustainable cycle.The hand-harvested salt crystals are then cleaned and packed, readied for delivery to customers across the world. Lunn Desert Salt are harvested twice each year. The salt harvested during summer is dried under a very hot sun quickly creating sun-tanned crystals.The winter harvest salt, dried over a longer period of time creating sparkling white crystals. Desert Salt is ideal for daily cooking as it not only lends extra flavour to the dishes, but it is also rich in minerals that are important in maintaining a healthy lifestyle. Lunn Salt is Fair Trade Certified salt. Hand-Harvested in sustainable way, Lunn Desert Salt is completely free of micro-plastics found in sea salt.'}, {'_id': '1250307', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': ''}]

[{'_id': '1236865', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Our rice comes from the Sona Masuri BPT 5204 variety of paddy cultivated by small and marginal farmers practicing chemical pesticide free agriculture in the Krishna irrigated region of the Raichur district in Karnataka. These farmers adopt the System of Rice Intensification (SRI) technique, which greatly reduces the water footprint of the crop. The paddy is stringently tested for quality parameters like moisture content and percentage of broken rice. The procured paddy is then aged for 18 months to further reduce the moisture content before it is milled into rice. Carefully curated ageing ensures that the rice has an optimum level of moisture translating into a higher yield of the cooked product.'}, {'_id': '1250230', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Sona Masuri Unpolished Brown Rice 5Kg'}]

It is ensured that Safe Harvest’s Tur Dal does not go through any polishing or artificial colouring which would otherwise compromise the nutrition content in the dal. You can use our tur to make a classic dal fry which would surely find its way onto your list of comfort foods within no time. Apart from the traditional recipes, our Tur Dal could also be used for making healthy snack alternatives like Tur Dal paranthas and khichdis which would not only be delicious but also add to your daily protein intake. While you prepare enticing dishes with our dal, we at Safe Harvest will ensure that no compromises are made on the quality and safety of the product."}, {'_id': '1249446', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Tur Dal 1Kg'}]

[{'_id': '1236475', 'specification': 'About', 'value': '\r\nOur wheat is cultivated by small and marginal women farmers practicing rain-fed agriculture in the tribal region of the Dewas district in Madhya Pradesh. Dewas is in Malwa, a region famous for its superior variety of wheat.The farmers we work with are part of Ram Rahim Pragati Producer Company Limited (RRPPCL), a Farmer Producer Organization owned and run by 4000 tribal women practicing chemical pesticide free agriculture. The choicest of grains procured from these women farmers are then slowly ground in Chakkis. Slow grinding generates less heat and helps retain fiber, proteins and other essential nutrients that are otherwise lost. Safe storage and minimal processing ensure that we bring all that is healthy and wholesome from her farm to your kitchen! We recommend that you add more water to the dough to get softer Rotis.'}, {'_id': '1249448', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Wheat Daliya 500G'}]

[{'_id': '1236705', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'If you are looking for healthier alternatives for rice, Safe Harvest’s Little Millet would be the product for you. After being ethically procured from small and marginal farmers practicing rain-fed agriculture in Virudhunagar district of Tamil Nadu, our Little Millet has been minimally processed, safely stored and hygienically packed at our processing centres. It is ensured that Safe Harvest’s Little Millet does not go through any polishing or artificial colouring which would otherwise compromise the nutrition content in the product. Millets are known to highly nutritious, easily digestible and rich in proteins, calcium and other minerals. When compared with rice, Little Millet has 13% less carbohydrates, is gluten free and has lower levels of glucose. Little millet has high fibre content and is largely beneficial for weight loss and gastric health. It could be used to substitute rice in making idly, upma, dosas and several rice items. The consumption of millets not only makes you healthier but also helps farmers practice more sustainable agriculture. Millets, unlike paddy and wheat, are not water intensive crops and would lead to conservation of water right from the farm gate.'}, {'_id': '1249838', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Little Millet Rice 500G'}]

[{'_id': '1236467', 'specification': 'About', 'value': '\r\nSafe Harvest’s Moong Dal is high in protein, fibre and amino acids and is the healthy and safe alternative that you have been looking for. After being ethically procured from a farmer’s collective in Netrang, Gujarat, our Moong Dal has been minimally processed, safely stored and hygienically packed at our processing centres. It is ensured that Safe Harvest’s moong dal does not go through any polishing or artificial colouring which would otherwise compromise the nutrition content in the dal. You can use our moong to make a classic dal tadka which would surely find its way onto your list of comfort foods within no time. Apart from the traditional recipes, our moong dal could also be used for making healthy snack alternatives like moong dal kachoris, bhajiyas and ladoos which would not only be tasty but also add to your daily protein intake. While you prepare enticing dishes with our moong dal, we at Safe Harvest will ensure that no compromises are made on the quality and safety of the product.'}, {'_id': '1249444', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Moong Dal 500G'}]

[{'_id': '1233162', 'specification': 'About', 'value': "Unpolished or brown rice is different from white rice in that the second layer, which is a reddish-brown thin skin hugging the rice seed, is left on.

[{'_id': '1236703', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'If you are looking for healthier alternatives for rice, Safe Harvest’s Kodo Millet would be the product for you. After being ethically procured from small and marginal farmers practicing rain-fed agriculture in Virudhunagar district of Tamil Nadu, our Kodo Millet has been minimally processed, safely stored and hygienically packed at our processing centres. It is ensured that Safe Harvest’s Kodo Millet does not go through any polishing or artificial colouring which would otherwise compromise the nutrition content in the product. Millets are known to highly nutritious, easily digestible and rich in proteins, calcium and other minerals. When compared with rice, Kodo Millet has 13% less carbohydrates, is gluten free and has lower levels of glucose. Kodo Millet could be used to substitute rice in making idly, upma, dosas and several rice items. The consumption of millets not only makes you healthier but also helps farmers practice more sustainable agriculture. Millets, unlike paddy and wheat, are not water intensive crops and would lead to conservation of water right from the farm gate.'}, {'_id': '1249837', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Kodo Millet Rice 500G'}]

p_spec: [{'_id': '1233094', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'An amber coloured resin extracted from the root or stem of a perennial plant, Hing plays many roles in many cultures. Scientifically called Ferula Assafoetida, Hing has been used as widely as in ancient Persia, Greece, Africa and India. From being used in black magic or warding away the evil eye to soothing stomach ailments, this spice has significant contribution to cultures around the world. p_name: Desert Salt Sum Har Sha 100 GM
p_spec:
[{'_id': '1233432', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'USAGE: Healthy Salt For Daily Cooking, Salads, Fruits, Juices & Health Drinks.
No Anti-Caking Agent, Free From Micro-Plastics, Traditionally Hand-Harvested, Raw- Not Processed.
RICH IN MINERALS: Lunn Desert salt is rich in minerals that are important in maintaining a healthy lifestyle like Potassium,Calcium, Iodine, Magnesium, Iron, Phosphorus & Sulphate.
CERTIFIED: Vegan, Gluten Free, Organic Harvest, Non- GMO, Fair Market, True Source & Halal
MILD IN TASTE & LOW ON SODIUM: Being A Mild Salt, It Brings Out Authentic Flavours In Your Food.
DESERT SALT HARVEST PROCESS: The Great Indian Desert, also known as the Thar Desert, situated in the state of Rajasthan, India is the 9th largest subtropical desert in the world. Deep beneath its glistening hot sands, large pools of water form when the rare rains arrive during the monsoon season. As the water seeps down, it combines with the mineral rich desert salt to form a thick saline mixture.This is pumped up and left to dry in the salt pans, creating dunes of one of the purest forms of salts found anywhere. Monsoon rains replenish the water levels each season creating a sustainable cycle.The hand-harvested salt crystals are then cleaned and packed, readied for delivery to customers across the world. Lunn Desert Salt are harvested twice each year. The salt harvested during summer is dried under a very hot sun quickly creating sun-tanned crystals.The winter harvest salt, dried over a longer period of time creating sparkling white crystals. Desert Salt is ideal for daily cooking as it not only lends extra flavour to the dishes, but it is also rich in minerals that are important in maintaining a healthy lifestyle. Lunn Salt is Fair Trade Certified salt. Hand-Harvested in sustainable way, Lunn Desert Salt is completely free of micro-plastics found in sea salt.'}, {'_id': '1250305', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': ''}]

[{'_id': '1236871', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Our rice comes from the Sona Masuri BPT 5204 variety of paddy cultivated by small and marginal farmers practicing chemical pesticide free agriculture in the Krishna irrigated region of the Raichur district in Karnataka. These farmers adopt the System of Rice Intensification (SRI) technique, which greatly reduces the water footprint of the crop. The paddy is stringently tested for quality parameters like moisture content and percentage of broken rice. The procured paddy is then aged for 12 months to further reduce the moisture content before it is milled into rice. Carefully curated ageing ensures that the rice has an optimum level of moisture translating into a higher yield of the cooked product.'}, {'_id': '1250233', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Sona Masuri Raw Rice 12 Months 5Kg'}]

[{'_id': '1236667', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Our wheat is cultivated by small and marginal women farmers practicing rain-fed agriculture in the tribal region of the Dewas district in Madhya Pradesh. Dewas is in Malwa, a region famous for its superior variety of wheat.The farmers we work with are part of Ram Rahim Pragati Producer Company Limited (RRPPCL), a Farmer Producer Organization owned and run by 4000 tribal women practicing chemical pesticide free agriculture. The choicest of grains procured from these women farmers are then slowly ground in Chakkis. Slow grinding generates less heat and helps retain fiber, proteins and other essential nutrients that are otherwise lost. Safe storage and minimal processing ensure that we bring all that is healthy and wholesome from her farm to your kitchen! We recommend that you add more water to the dough to get softer Rotis.'}, {'_id': '1249787', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'Whole Wheat Atta 5Kg'}]

p_spec: [{'_id': '1235763', 'specification': 'Description', 'value': 'KOLAN PET STAINS & ODOUR REMOVER HARD SURFACES 700ML'}, {'_id': '1235764', 'specification': 'About', 'value': 'Kolan Pet Stains and Odour Remover (For Hard Surfaces) cleanses shines, disinfects and kills practically all harmful germs, viruses and bacteria from the surface. Expertly removes stinky yellow pet urine, faeces, vomit and other organic spills. It eliminates all odour at the source. Safe and ideal for all areas of your home and office hard surface which are water safe. PROPRIETARY MULTI ENZYME FORMULA Enzymes are proteins, composed of hundreds of amino acids, which are produced by living organisms. These enzymes are excellent biological catalysts and are very specific in nature. The ‘MAGIC’ is derived from the fact that our unique multi-enzyme formula, developed in New Zealand, allows all four enzymes (Proteases, Amylases, Lipases, Cellulases) to co-exist together. It provides a complete and hygiene cleaning solution by destroying the entire stain and odour in one application thus eliminating the need for harmful caustic chemicals found in common household cleaners.'}]
p_tags: KOLAN PET STAINS & ODOUR REMOVER HARD SURFACES 700ML
